TEXT 440 -80 Left 2 ;Re forms a voltage divider with RL. If we want maximum swing of\n+/- 15V, Re must be chosen equal to RL: \nVe = -30 Re/(Re+RL)\n \nThis also means the signal can swing up to about 14.8V - or Q1 will be \nsaturated.\n \nDC analysis:\nVoltage across Re is 30V, with a quescient current of 3.7A\nQ1 base current is about 37mA.\nRe dissipates 3.7^2*8 = 110W, and Q1 another 3.7*15 = 55W.\n \nAC analysis:\nTo get the desired output of 10W into 8 ohm, the output signal must \nbe about 9vrms, i.e. 13V peak.\nTherefore the amplifier needs to swing to +/- 13 volts. \nAt peak, the voltage across Re is -30-13 = -43 volts, \nand the current is 5.4A.\nThe base drive needs to be then at least 50mA, hence the \nhefty current source.
